<paragraph blockId="41.[160,1156,1528,1692]" box="[160,300,1528,1553]" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[160,1156,1528,1692]" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klausewitz" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[160,467,1564,1588]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Acanthocercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="41" pageNumber="811" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ugandaensis">
<emphasis box="[160,467,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Acanthocercus ugandaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from unspecified localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1007,1097,1564,1588]" name="Uganda" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, and since, the description has not been recorded elsewhere. Herein, we recognize it from 
<collectingCountry box="[160,250,1633,1657]" name="Rwanda" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
(Cyamudongo), 
<collectingCountry box="[440,508,1633,1657]" name="Kenya" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[522,643,1633,1657]" country="Kenya" name="Kakamega" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Kakamega</collectingRegion>
, Nairobi) and 
<collectingCountry box="[804,903,1633,1657]" name="Tanzania" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(Mount Meru) as well (
<figureCitation box="[167,274,1668,1692]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="36.[160,225,1253,1276]" captionTargetBox="[178,1138,142,1222]" captionTargetId="figure-183@36.[178,1138,142,1222]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="Figure 15. Holotype (ZMB 23906) of Acanthocercus kiwuensis, from Kissenji, Rwanda." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5174483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5174483/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="811">Figure 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[160,1156,141,305]" box="[160,405,141,166]" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,405,141,166]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">Habitat and ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[160,1156,141,305]" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klausewitz" baseAuthorityYear="1957" box="[160,456,177,201]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Acanthocercus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ugandaensis">
<emphasis box="[160,456,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">Acanthocercus ugandaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a tree dweller and occurs in secondary dry forest, but also in plantations, large hedges along streets and on solitary trees in gardens (pers. observ. E. Greenbaum). There is no information about the social structure of the species, but solitary specimens only were trapped by the senior author around 
<collectingRegion box="[818,932,281,305]" country="Kenya" name="Kakamega" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">Kakamega</collectingRegion>
forest, 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1086,281,305]" name="Kenya" pageId="42" pageNumber="812">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
